00:51:02,742 --> 00:51:31,601
so it's by bypassing that keeping our attention on what it is we're experiencing as arising and passing away see not me not mine that there comes the experience of who we really are now the Buddha referred to himself as the Tathagata which means the one who's transcended so there is within us this Buddha nature this intuitive awareness you'll find it referred to in various ways

367
00:51:32,172 --> 00:52:00,963
and really to experience that in itself is our aim because once that's known the path leading to the end of suffering is open wide that's what it says but once you know that then it's you can't know it no well it's now that's the interesting thing isn't it because in your meditation this intuitive awareness we're exercising

